Freud has come under some criticism recently.
Always been.
Do you still feel that most of his material, and I'm talking as a strict layman now, I'm just curious, but he has been, how do you, that's a general question.
You know, my opinion is very simple.
History will establish it.
I don't have to worry about it.
I think I've accepted what he presented as a valid and useful, but that doesn't mean that I don't think he was a crook, and some of the people are willing to say.
I think he did what he thought was, he gave what he thought was understandable and meaningful.
But in any science, we don't think he had the last word, and so I'm not terribly worried about it.

critical for Freud.
